{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"metadata":{"title":"FileInfoRef","externalID":"s:3GIO11FileInfoRefV","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"FileInfoRef","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"FileInfoRef"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure","role":"symbol"},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(_:)-2cavy","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(_:)-3ddvs","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(_:)-6zand","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(_:)-730jj","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(_:)-7bn4z","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"]},{"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/ptr"],"generated":true},{"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/unowned(_:)"]},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/FileInfoProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/GWeakCapturing-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/fileinforef"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Stores information about a file system object referenced by a [iface","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/File"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"FileInfoRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Functionality for manipulating basic metadata for files. ","type":"text"},{"code":"GFileInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"implements methods for getting information that all files should","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"contain, and allows for manipulation of extended attributes.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"file-attributes.html"},{"text":" document for more","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information on how GIO handles file attributes."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To obtain a "},{"code":"GFileInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for a [iface"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/File","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"], use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.File.query_info"},{"text":"] (or its async variant). To obtain a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GFileInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for a file input or output stream, use [method"},{"code":"Gio.FileInputStream.query_info","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or [method"},{"code":"Gio.FileOutputStream.query_info","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] (or their async variants).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To change the actual attributes of a file, you should then set the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attribute in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFileInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" and call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.File.set_attributes_from_info"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or [method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.File.set_attributes_async","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] on a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GFile","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"However, not all attributes can be changed in the file. For instance,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the actual size of a file cannot be changed via [method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.FileInfo.set_size","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You may call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.File.query_settable_attributes"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.File.query_writable_namespaces"},{"type":"text","text":"] to discover the settable attributes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a particular file at runtime."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The direct accessors, such as [method"},{"code":"Gio.FileInfo.get_name","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], are slightly more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"optimized than the generic attribute accessors, such as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"Gio.FileInfo.get_attribute_byte_string","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"].This optimization will matter"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"only if calling the API in a tight loop.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is an error to call these accessors without specifying their required file","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"attributes when creating the ","type":"text"},{"code":"GFileInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Use","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"Gio.FileInfo.has_attribute","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] or [method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.FileInfo.list_attributes","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to check what attributes are specified for a "},{"code":"GFileInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileAttributeMatcher","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] allows for searching through a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFileInfo"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for attributes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFileInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFileInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfo","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef"},{"text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GFileInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject14GWeakCapturingP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://GIO/4GLib14PointerWrapperP":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","type":"unresolvable","title":"GLib.PointerWrapper"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/FileInfoRef/GWeakCapturing-Implementations":{"kind":"article","title":"GWeakCapturing Implementations","abstract":[],"role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/fileinforef\/gweakcapturing-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileInfoRef\/GWeakCapturing-Implementations"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/FileInfoRef/init(cPointer:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unsafe typed initialiser."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Do not use unless you know the underlying data type the pointer points to